## B.3 Comparison of ODE Solvers  

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[174, 764, 824, 808]]<|/det|>
The comparison results of using the Euler or midpoint ODE solver during F5- TTS inference are shown in Tab.5. The Euler is inherently faster (first- order) and performs slightly better typically for larger NFE inference with Sway Sampling (otherwise the Euler solver results in degradation).  

<|ref|>sub_title<|/ref|><|det|>[[174, 823, 530, 839]]<|/det|>
## B.4 Sway Sampling Effectiveness on Base Models  

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[174, 849, 824, 905]]<|/det|>
From Tab.6, it is clear that our Sway Sampling strategy for test- time flow steps consistently improves the zero- shot generation performance in aspects of faithfulness to prompt text (WER) and speaker similarity (SIM). The gain of applying Sway Sampling to E2 TTS [36] proves that our Sway Sampling strategy is universally applicable to existing flow matching based TTS models.

