<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[173, 461, 825, 546]]<|/det|>
We note that a higher WER compared to the results on commonly used test sets is partially due to mispronunciation (yogis to yojus, cavorts to caverns, etc.). The high Deletion rate indicates a word- skipping phenomenon when our model encounters a stack of repeating words. The low Insertion rate makes it clear that our model is free of endless repetition. We further emphasize that prompts from different speakers will spell very distinct utterances, where the ASR model transcribes correctly for one, and fails for another (e.g. quokkas to Cocos).

